WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Alright, well thank you everyone for attending. This is such a large crowd, I'm very excited.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.000
What we're going to look at today is a new package for making dashboards by RStudio called Flex Dashboard.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.000
And we could start just by looking at some Flex Dashboards to see what these things are.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:24.000
These are all Flex Dashboards. You can see that they're dashboards, primarily visual displays of data.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:29.000
And they're geared to help you very quickly understand or comprehend a data set.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:34.000
If we look at what's in these dashboards, you'll notice there's some ggplot2 graphics.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:40.000
There's some base graphics, although not that many on this page because base graphics aren't as sexy as they could be.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.000
But then there's also interactive things. So for example, here's a Flex Dashboard.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:52.000
It has some HTML widgets based on high charter, which means you can hover over things and read off specific values.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
There's some lightweight interactivity going on here.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Here's another Flex Dashboard that also has this HTML widget based interactivity.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.000
It also has Shiny components buried in the dashboard.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.000
So we could, for example, use a drop down menu to select a different city to look at.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:11.000
And the whole dashboard updates. And it's using Shiny in the background to do this.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:16.000
And now we're looking at a different city, we can move a slider and that sort of thing.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:21.000
There's also multiple pages in this dashboard or other dashboards.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:24.000
So we can look at things over time.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.000
So the idea here behind Flex Dashboards is pretty simple.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:41.000
It's just a way to display graphics, tables, a little bit of navigation, a little bit of layout organization

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:46.000
to create an administrative dashboard for looking at data.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:52.000
The delivery of Flex Dashboards is the same as any dashboard.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:55.000
It's your portal into a dataset.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:02:00.000
But on the back end, Flex Dashboards have some things that make it attractive to you, the developer.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:06.000
And those things include, first of all, a Flex Dashboard is created with R Markdown.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:10.000
So if you know how to use R Markdown, you can create Flex Dashboards.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:13.000
The syntax is the same. And if you don't know how to use R Markdown,

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:19.000
Markdown syntax is so easy to learn that by the end of this webinar you'll be able to make your own Flex Dashboards.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:24.000
For the most part. There might be some things I'm not going to repeat about R Markdown here.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:29.000
The other benefit of using R Markdown is, once you create your Flex Dashboard,

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:33.000
it's just an HTML document, an HTML document that was created with R Markdown.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:37.000
And you can use any of the channels that you already use to publish R Markdown documents

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:40.000
to publish your Flex Dashboard. So you can put in RPUBs, for example,

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
or maybe RStudio Connect, or even ShinyApps.io to publish your Dashboard

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.000
and get it out there for other people to see.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:52.000
The other thing about Flex Dashboards is that they're going to do some work for you in the background.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:58.000
Flex Dashboards automatically resize the components inside the Dashboard to fit your user's browser window.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Or even if your user looks at the Dashboard on a mobile device,

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:05.000
it'll do resizing to make sure that the Dashboard looks intelligent on their mobile device as well.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:10.000
So that's all things you don't have to worry about. Flex Dashboard is going to do it for you.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:14.000
And since Flex Dashboards are R Markdown documents,

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:18.000
and since R Markdown can deliver anything that you can create with R,

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Flex Dashboards can also deliver anything that you create with R.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:25.000
You can make it with R, you can display it in your Dashboard.

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:28.000
And that's a wide variety of things. You have your interactive HTML widgets,

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
that's JavaScript-based visualizations. You have your base graphics, last graphics,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:35.000
ggplot2 graphics, put tables in there.

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.000
And then we'll see that Flex Dashboards even come with some of their own bells and whistles

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:41.000
that you can use inside your Dashboards.

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:46.000
And then finally, like we highlighted, Flex Dashboards are Shiny compatible.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.000
So if you want to have some deep reactivity in your Dashboard,

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:54.000
if you want to provide R scripts and R instructions that your users can trigger

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:57.000
just by pushing a button and moving a slider, you can do that.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:02.000
You can really curate their analysis experience inside this Dashboard

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:04.000
by combining Flex Dashboards with Shiny.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:10.000
Given all that, the Flex Dashboard package is actually very simple,

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:13.000
and there's not too much for us to cover.

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:17.000
What I hope to do here with this webinar is to teach you enough about Flex Dashboards

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:21.000
that when the webinar is over, you can go off and make your own Dashboard today.

